  metadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-java/index.json:23:    "description" : "Plexus Java is the Java-language module of Plexus Languages, providing JVM utilities for reading JPMS module descriptors and deriving module names from Java artifacts. It also includes Java version parsing helpers used by Maven and Plexus tooling when inspecting Java libraries.",
  metadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-java/index.json:37:    "description" : "Plexus Java is the Java-language module of Plexus Languages, providing JVM utilities for reading JPMS module descriptors and deriving module names from Java artifacts. It also includes Java version parsing helpers used by Maven and Plexus tooling when inspecting Java libraries.",
  metadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-io/index.json:9:    "description" : "Plexus IO provides reusable I/O resource abstractions, file selectors, file mappers, and archive or compressed-resource collection utilities for Plexus-based Java applications. It helps tools enumerate, filter, transform, and read file, URL, ZIP, and compressed resources while preserving resource attributes.",
