.discovery.PlexusXmlComponentDiscoverer\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-8/reachability-metadata.json:1008:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.DefaultPlexusContainer\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-java/index.json:8:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Java is the Java-language module of Plexus Languages, providing JVM utilities for reading JPMS module descriptors and deriving module names from Java artifacts. It also includes Java version parsing helpers used by Maven and Plexus tooling when inspecting Java libraries.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-java/index.json:23:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Java is the Java-language module of Plexus Languages, providing JVM utilities for reading JPMS module descriptors and deriving module names from Java artifacts. It also includes Java version parsing helpers used by Maven and Plexus tooling when inspecting Java libraries.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-java/index.json:37:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Java is the Java-language module of Plexus Languages, providing JVM utilities for reading JPMS module descriptors and deriving module names from Java artifacts. It also includes Java version parsing helpers used by Maven and Plexus tooling when inspecting Java libraries.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-io/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Plexus IO provides reusable I/O resource abstractions, file selectors, file mappers, and archive or compressed-resource collection utilities for Plexus-based Java applications. It helps tools enumerate, filter, transform, and read file, URL, ZIP, and compressed resources while preserving resource attributes.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-10/reachability-metadata.json:91:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.DefaultPlexusContainer\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-10/reachability-metadata.json:170:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.DefaultPlexusContainer\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-10/reachability-metadata.json:174:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.PlexusContainerManager$1\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-10/reachability-metadata.json:176:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.PlexusContainerManager\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-10/reachability-metadata.json:199:            \"org.codehaus.plexus.MutablePlexusContainer\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-10/reachability-metadata.json:208:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.SimplePlexusContainerManager\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-10/reachability-metadata.json:219:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.SimplePlexusContainerManager\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-10/reachability-metadata.json:379:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.component.discovery.PlexusXmlComponentDiscoverer\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-10/reachability-metadata.json:871:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.personality.plexus.PlexusLifecycleHandler\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-10/reachability-metadata.json:883:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.personality.plexus.PlexusLifecycleHandler\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-10/reachability-metadata.json:1111:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.component.discovery.PlexusXmlComponentDiscoverer\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-10/reachability-metadata.json:1183:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.personality.plexus.PlexusLifecycleHandler\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-10/reachability-metadata.json:1308:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.component.discovery.PlexusXmlComponentDiscoverer\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-10/reachability-metadata.json:1314:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.component.discovery.PlexusXmlComponentDiscoverer\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-10/reachability-metadata.json:1320:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.DefaultPlexusContainer\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Container Default is the original Plexus inversion-of-control container implementation used to discover, configure, compose, and manage Plexus components. It provides component descriptors, lifecycle handling, dependency injection, configuration conversion, logging hooks, and embeddable container APIs for Java applications.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/index.json:23:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Container Default is the original Plexus inversion-of-control container implementation used to discover, configure, compose, and manage Plexus components. It provides component descriptors, lifecycle handling, dependency injection, configuration conversion, logging hooks, and embeddable container APIs for Java applications.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/index.json:38:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Container Default is the original Plexus inversion-of-control container implementation used to discover, configure, compose, and manage Plexus components. It provides component descriptors, lifecycle handling, dependency injection, configuration conversion, logging hooks, and embeddable container APIs for Java applications.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/index.json:52:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Container Default is the original Plexus inversion-of-control container implementation used to discover, configure, compose, and manage Plexus components. It provides component descriptors, lifecycle handling, dependency injection, configuration conversion, logging hooks, and embeddable container APIs for Java applications.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-interactivity-api/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Interactivity API provides interfaces and default components for prompting users and handling console input and output within Plexus-based tools. It exposes Prompter, InputHandler, and OutputHandler abstractions plus simple default implementations used by Maven and Plexus components.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-cipher/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Cipher is a Java component for encrypting and decrypting strings with passphrases and Base64-encoded output. It also supports Maven/Plexus-style decorated encrypted values wrapped in braces so callers can detect, decorate, and undecorate stored secrets.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-7/reachability-metadata.json:91:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.DefaultPlexusContainer\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-7/reachability-metadata.json:117:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.DefaultPlexusContainer\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-7/reachability-metadata.json:121:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.PlexusContainerManager$1\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-7/reachability-metadata.json:123:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.PlexusContainerManager\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-7/reachability-metadata.json:129:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.SimplePlexusContainerManager\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-7/reachability-metadata.json:140:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.SimplePlexusContainerManager\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-7/reachability-metadata.json:300:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.component.discovery.PlexusXmlComponentDiscoverer\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-7/reachability-metadata.json:588:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.personality.plexus.PlexusLifecycleHandler\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-7/reachability-metadata.json:600:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.personality.plexus.PlexusLifecycleHandler\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-7/reachability-metadata.json:828:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.component.discovery.PlexusXmlComponentDiscoverer\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-7/reachability-metadata.json:900:      \"type\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.personality.plexus.PlexusLifecycleHandler\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-7/reachability-metadata.json:1002:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.component.discovery.PlexusXmlComponentDiscoverer\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-container-default/1.0-alpha-7/reachability-metadata.json:1008:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.codehaus.plexus.DefaultPlexusContainer\"\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-resources/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Resources provides a component API for locating and loading resources from the filesystem, classpath, JAR files, and URLs. It is used by Plexus-based Java applications and Maven-related tooling to access resources through a common resource manager abstraction.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-xml/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Plexus XML provides utility classes for reading, writing, and manipulating XML in Maven and Plexus-based projects. It includes XML writer helpers, stream reader and writer utilities, XPP3 DOM support, and XML pull-parser classes.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-xml/index.json:29:    \"description\" : \"Plexus XML provides utility classes for reading, writing, and manipulating XML used by Maven and Plexus-based projects. It includes XML writer helpers, stream reader/writer utilities, XPP3 DOM support, and pull-parser classes extracted from the older plexus-utils package.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-utils/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Utils provides shared Java utility classes for working with strings, files, command lines, XML, and related infrastructure tasks. Maven and Plexus-based projects use it for reusable helpers around IO, reflection, collections, and process execution.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-utils/index.json:63:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Utils provides common Java utilities historically used by Apache Maven and Plexus-based projects. It includes helpers for file and IO handling, string manipulation, command-line execution, DAG processing, introspection, and XML utilities.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-utils/index.json:77:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Utils provides shared Java utility classes for working with strings, files, command lines, XML, and related infrastructure tasks. Maven and Plexus-based projects use it for reusable helpers around IO, reflection, collections, and process execution.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-utils/index.json:91:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Utils provides common Java utility classes for working with strings, files, command lines, XML, and related tasks. Maven and Plexus-based projects use it to share reusable helpers for IO, reflection, collections, and process execution.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-utils/index.json:105:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Utils provides common Java utility classes for working with strings, files, command lines, XML, and related tasks. It is used by Maven and Plexus-based projects to share reusable helpers for IO, reflection, collections, and process execution.\",\nmetadata/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-utils/index.json:119:    \"description\" : \"Plexus Utils provides common Java utility classes for working with strings, files, command lines, XML, and related tasks. It is used by Maven an